<HEADLINE>
Vanilla Nethack: &quot;Shuddering&quot; upon reading tele scroll
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<POST>
<POSTER> s...@deathquaker.org </POSTER>
<POSTDATE> 2007-08-23T11:22:00 </POSTDATE>
A little while ago, I got my monk in some trouble where she was a
little more surrounded than she ought to have been down in the Gnomish
Mines. I had a couple scrolls of teleport so I thought I'd try
teleporting away. I read one and it merely said, &quot;You shudder a
moment.&quot;

I'd never seen that before except standing upon teleportation (or
other kinds of magical) *traps*. I wondered if it was maybe some sort
of quasi-magic resistance the monk had, though that usually doesn't
stop magic you activate on your own. AFAIK, the scrolls were NOT
cursed (uncursed, IIRC; I had altar ID'd them).

My stupidity (beyond the initial stupidity of letting myself get
surrounded in the first place) was deciding to try it again  --
thinking maybe it was a random event, perhaps a function of luck. But
the same thing happened and.... the monsters killed me.

What causes that? Is it a monk thing, a luck thing, or what? Just need
to know what to keep track of in case I need a tele scroll in a jam
again sometime. Of course, working on not getting surrounded is my
own, separate issue. :)

Thanks,

Death Quaker
</POST>
